The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         BRIEFS
                  
	Midnapore, April 28: A CPM activist was killed and another seriously injured when Jharkhand Party (Aditya Group) supporters fired on a procession of over 200 motorcycle-borne CPM men in a village in West Midnapores Lalgarh this afternoon.    
	Peosi Chalak, 23, a member of the CPMs Kanchannagar branch committee, died on the spot.        
	Calcutta: Fifteen people, including two children, were injured when armed CPM and RSP supporters clashed at Amjhara in Basanti in South 24-Parganas, 70km from Calcutta. The children, aged 12 and 13, were struck by bomb splinters. The RSP has called a Basanti bandh on Tuesday and Trinamul has supported it.                                                                                                                                                                   
